 {"id":"charmed_rust-64r","title":"Epic: Add WASM Support for lipgloss/glamour","description":"# Epic: Add WASM Support for lipgloss/glamour

## Overview
WASM support enables using lipgloss and glamour in browsers and other WASM runtimes. This opens use cases like interactive documentation, playground sites, and server-side rendering.

## Business Justification
- New Markets: Browser-based TUI/styling
- Documentation: Interactive examples on web
- Marketing: Demo sites showcase library
- Innovation: New use cases emerge

## Technical Approach
1. Audit platform-specific code
2. Add wasm feature flag
3. Create HTML/CSS output backend
4. Set up wasm-pack build
